    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Dear friend,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I received the current weekly only yesterday. Many<lb/> distractions
                and delays made it impossible for me — in this<lb/> big Sodom — to send it along to
                you yesterday. I beg of you<lb/> to take all changes into consideration. For greater
                accuracy<lb/> I repeat the more important right here.</p>
            <p>p.1. From establishment of Secure<add>?</add> Temple Cyrus</p>
            <p>p.2</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">In the future I shall be careful that the manuscript<lb/> be more
                carefully edited, in order that you might be saved the<lb/> trouble. Consider how
                one's care in literary work must be di-<lb/>vided <del>?</del> among material,
                thought, style, and language. I<lb/> can well say of myself (in the language of a
                Hebrew proverb)<lb/> “I have labored and have achieved, believe him”. I am well<lb/>
                satisfied with my work. <sic>Eevn</sic> if the Occident should appear two<lb/> days
                late, the looks of this composition will overbalance that.<lb/> I therefore beg for
                the greatest care. I especially ask to<lb/> be careful that the appendix appear
                exactly on page 1, following<lb/> that which is here written on page 2, and that the
                end, the<lb/> uniting articles of faith, come at the end, Also that the notes<lb/>
                and references appear in the proper spot. It would be well<lb/> to send copies also
                to non-subscribes.</p>
            <p>p.3</p>
            <p>“And they said” —— they made all alike.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>p.4</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Please be good enough to send me at one several copies<lb/> of No.
                17, and also fifty copies of the issues of <date>November</date> and<lb/>
                <date>December</date>, by express.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">But the chief consideration is that you print the con-<lb/>clusion,
                for it would be terrible if this were not done. At<lb/> least you should print the
                conclusion to II, and then</p>
            <p>I hope you will fulfill my wishes.</p>
            <p>Again I beg you to be careful, very careful. Show me the<lb/> personal consideration
                frequently to go to the printer's when<lb/> he is working on this. “The work is more
                important than the<lb/> worker”.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">How is the English translation getting on?</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">A— sends you nothing, then how shall I send the Penta-<lb/>techs to
                you</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I beg of you to be sure to transmit the enclosed letter<lb/> to the
                    <persName>Mohel Friedmann</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">With sincere friendship, very devotedly,</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <persName role="author">Jonah Bondi</persName>
            </p>
